The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques applied to medical imaging, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of convolutional sparse coding and deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also deals with multimodal image synthesis, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category. The use of unpaired data and the hetero-domain image alignment term suggest that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper also deals with optimization techniques, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) category.
